fields.address: Keyuan Avenue, 1th, Shenzhen Bay port, Shenzhen, China
fields.cs_description: Urwork Ali cloud enjoys a beautiful location and offers a great view over Shenzhen Bay. As both the design and the location are meant to inspire, the community at Urwork Ali cloud is composed of hard working professionals, talented freelancers and innovative startups. People from all over the world made Urwork Ali cloud their home. Communication is enhanced, as the shared working area provides the ideal coworking environment. Private offices are also available, depending on your needs. Among the services available you will also get professional assistance from the staff members. Enjoy the perks of working in a multinational office, next to like minded professionals and talented people. You can have unlimited access to all amenities, as everything is included in the convenient monthly fee.

fields.address: Yuanxing technology building No.1 Sogping Rd. North district , High tech park (north), Nanshan, Shenzhen, China
fields.cs_description:
The first coworking space in Shenzhen, China, SZTeam offers a community and shared workspace environment for techies, startups, creatives, entrepreneurs and other professional independents within the wide industry.

Flexible membership options are offered at SZTeam where you can choose according to your work needs. Every membership includes full use of the facilities such as a fully stocked kitchen, use of the relaxation area, super speedy internet plus extra perks for foreign members from Chinese translators to members only discounts.

Share and learn alongside the SZTeam community and partake in collaborative opportunities aside from individual work focus. Pick up a new skill or innovate your ideas for collective professional growth.

fields.address: 1 Kefa Road, 4F Huafuyang Building, Shenzhen, China
fields.cs_description:
Founded by a group of young entrepreneurs, SimplyWork is Shenzhen’s most dreambitious co-working space. Currently we have 7 spaces (22,300 square meters in total) around Shenzhen area. We provide comfortable collaborative spaces, local and international venture capital resources, professional and thoughtful entrepreneurial services, unique and inspiring events, and exciting casual atmosphere. We strongly believe in the advantages that stem from shared work spaces and dynamic communities. By sharing resources, we’re playing an important role in the future of our planet’s well-being. 

We’re all about creating a wonderful space for our members and adding them to a dynamic community of thousands of people who’ve made us what we are today. In June 2016, SimplyWork has secured a 30M RMB A-round of venture funding from IDG Capital Partners, Huazhu Group and Vanke Group. We also have 200+ startups, 2000+ Whales aka members, 200+ famous investment institutions, 200+ partners, 10+ FA institutions and 20+ entrepreneurial supportive platforms along with us. 

Diversity or internationality is not a strategy. It is who we are. We have Whales aka members from over 30 countries, and all of them are dreamers, creators and doers. We don’t have a particular style, but we foster a vibrant and collaborative community to support and empower the success of our members. Come and join us! SimplyWork can’t wait to be your best buddy along your startup journey!

fields.address: Keyuanxi Building 23, 1 Kezhixi Road, Nanshan, Shenzhen, China
fields.cs_description:
Established on January 1st, 2015, SimplyWork is a welcoming and nurturing coworking brand based in Shenzhen, China.  Aimed at providing entrepreneurs with well-equipped facilities and thoughtful services, SimplyWork has 7 spaces available for now and will soon expand to 10 in diﬀerent districts  locally.

By the end of 2015, SimplyWork has been reported by around 30 main medias：Southern Metropolis Daily, Xinhua News Agency, CCTV, Guangdong TV and the like.

Within just a year and a half, over 300 startup teams (2000+ whales aka members in total) have been working here and more than 500 entrepreneurial activities have been hosted.  What’s more, we work closely with around 200 investment institutions and 30 professional ﬁnancial advisors all around the world in order to help the entrepreneurs here to ﬁnd their next investor or co-founder. We are also a bridge between 200 partners and those who are in need of services on legal advice, company registration, intellectual property, design, house renting, ticket booking,  etc.

Our joint endeavor and eﬃcient operation have made it a mile- stone that we secured a 30M RMB A-round of venture funding from IDG Capital Partners, Huazhu Group and Vanke Group in June, 2016.

fields.address: Qiao Xiang Lu, Shenzhen, China
fields.cs_description: ibaseoffice - Weixin Center coworking provides a cozy working environment for over 500 people. Located in Shenzhen’s Science and Technology Park, this working space has some important neighbors. Large companies such as Alibaba, Intel, Flextronics and other well known enterprises are located in the area. When it comes to office space, ibaseoffice - Weixin Center offers individual and shared offices for a high number of members. Each office can be customized according to your business needs and each of them features high class equipment: from furniture to high speed internet connection. Private offices are separated by glass walls, thus creating a modern look. Meeting rooms are available through booking. They are ideal for team meetings, project presentations and even interviews with potential employees. ibaseoffice - Weixin Center’s recreational area is the place where you can take a break from work and relax. You can sip a cup of coffee and get to know your colleagues better. After all, not everything in life is about work. Become a member today!

fields.address: Shennan Avenue, Shenzhen, China
fields.space_name: ibase - Shenzhen Garden Expo Creative Association
fields.cs_description: Shenzhen Garden Expo Creative Association will impress you in two ways. First, with its amazing location in the bamboo forest district, alongside to Shenzhen International Garden Flower Expo Park. Second, with its great features and style. The location combines perfectly the business area with the natural environment. Shenzhen Garden Expo Creative Association has the capacity to host 200 people. Freelancers, professionals, entrepreneurs and startups as welcomed to work on their projects here. Maybe one of the greatest benefits that this coworking space offers it the ability to customize the offices according to different business needs. A private office will provide you with the quiet you need in order to focus on your work. On the opposite side, a shared office will give you the chance to share your knowledge with like minded professionals and talented people. You never know who will give you the next business idea…When it comes to amenities, Shenzhen Garden Expo Creative Association offers everything you need in order to provide a comfortable environment and improve your experience. From office equipment to activities and access to the recreational area. Give this place a try and become a member today!

fields.address: Long Jing Lu, Shenzhen, China
fields.cs_description: Shenzhen Longjing welcomes you in a quiet atmosphere. The interior design is a beautiful combination of wood furniture and green details. Thus, it complements the outdoor landscape. Its creative design is meant to enhance inspiration and creativity. Shenzhen Longjing offers nine independent offices and numerous shared working spaces. The VIP rooms can accommodate up to 80 people, as they are perfect for team projects. Nothing is more important than communication when working with a large number of people. If you need special additions in your office, you don’t have to worry about making the changes yourself. All offices can be customized according to your business needs, as the team at Shenzhen Longjing will make sure you have everything you need. It is a flexible coworking space that promises to provide you all the comfort you need. At a convenient monthly fee you can enjoy working in a modern office equipped with top notch amenities. You have unlimited access to the recreational facilities and free coffee. What more can you wish for?

fields.address: 14 Calle el Escorial, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: Workshop PC provides coworking spaces in Malasaña neighborhood in Madrid, Spain. Whether you’re a freelancer or a start-up entrepreneur, you can find the office that best suits you, right here. Workshop PC has a variety of office spaces available for you, from private desks, shared desks, meeting rooms, workshop spaces, whatever you need. They promise to adapt accordingly. Apart from providing efficient and comfortable office spaces, they also offer a kitchen area where you can have your lunch break or make yourself a refreshing cup of coffee in the morning. With the printers, scanners and photocopiers available you have all you need for an efficient day. Are you ready to change your office space now?

fields.address: 24 Calle Fernando el Santo, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: workClub Madrid is a community of freelancers, start-up entrepreneurs and independent professionals that meet here every day to get their work done in a friendly and productive environment. It’s a great alternative to the isolating office you used to have working at home. This is a place where you can continue to enjoy your flexibility and independency. The bonus point workClub offers you is the chance to meet like-minded professionals like yourself and make some important connections for your business. You can choose from a variety of different office styles, private and shared spaces and meeting rooms. There’s also a lounge area where you can have your lunch break or initiate a conversation with your coworker, whichever you prefer. Check this coworking space out.

fields.address: Paseo del Rey, 4, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description:
Work case is located in one of the most accessible areas in Madrid. It is directly opposite the station of Principe Pio. While coworking in work case, your work productivity is oriented towards a professional level. Enjoy the use of a functional and modern space with personalized services to assist your daily work schedule.

Practicality is applied in the layout of the Workcase space. There are two levels, Plant 1 and Plant 2. In Plant 1 is where you can observe the coworking magic. Their coworking spaces are designed especially for the use of coworkers. This so it is comfortable and geared towards functionality. Plant 2 is where you can find The Grotto, a lounge seating area where you can rest with coffee and socialize.

A community of business, entrepreneurship, creatives and techies, the people at Workcase are from various professional backgrounds and together they concrete while networking among each other, developing and sharing new skills as well as knowledge. A component for successful coworking is how a wonderful community can work together to achieve results.

Stop by and visit them easily by commuting using the metro or bus.

fields.address: 13 Calle de José Ortega y Gasset, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: Work4us is a work center where individuals from different working environments and industries come together, sharing a coworking space. The coworking space is suitable for a small team, freelancers or independent professionals as it offers a comfortable, dynamic and friendly work environment. Here, you can choose from individual or shared desks, fully equipped with a storage area, internet, landline telephone and access to a meeting room. Work4us wants to cater to different working styles and needs, which is why they offer a variety of office space options and rates. Choosing a coworking space as your everyday office can also offer you the possibility to connect with different people, which will definitely benefit your start-up business. Come and see if Work4us is the right fit for you.

fields.address: 2 Calle de Silva, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: Work Lab Callo is a business center located right in the heart of Madrid, next to the Plaza de Callao and Grand Via. Because of its central location it has a great connection with public transport, so you won’t have to worry how to get to the office each morning. The offices here are comfortable and practical, fully equipped with everything you’ll need to have a productive day. All offices have a speedy internet connection, modern and comfortable furnishings and security installations. Other services available for you here are a receptionist service, fully equipped board rooms and meeting rooms, catering services, printing services, virtual offices and chill out areas. Are you ready to relocate your coworking space now?

fields.address: 11 Calle San Lorenzo, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description:
Village is a unique coworking space located in the heart Madrid, between Malasana and Chueca. Here you will find a XIX century Art Noveau building that hides all the features and amenities of the modern time office. This beautiful coworking space offers open spaces or private offices, depending on your tastes. Village is a place that brings together designers, social marketing professionals, advertising agencies and freelancers. All offices are furnished and equipped to the latest technology and member have access to the kitchen and dining area, as well as 24/7 access. You can enjoy the beautiful architecture of the city by taking a walk to one the restaurants that are in close proximity to Village. 

Come and join Village for the best experience of your life!

fields.address: 4 Calle Amor de Dios, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: Veidimanna Protum is a business center offering professional coworking spaces in Madrid, Spain. Here gathers a community of architects and other professionals from this industry. The design of this place is a perfect blending of a modern and comfortable style, it’s a unique working space for sure. The coworking space area offers shared and private offices fully equipped with all the needed facilities for your daily tasks to run smoothly and efficiently. Apart from the coworking spaces, Veidimanna Protum also offers a lounging area where you can have your lunch breaks or socialize with your coworkers. Come and join this community of professionals, you will definitely fit right in.

fields.address: 5 Calle Duque de Rivas, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description:
A melting pot for ideas and knowledge, then throw in a good dose of passion and plenty of innovative and interesting people, and you have utopic US.  This is where it all happens for those that want somewhere to plonk their laptop whilst doing some work in the bustling heart of fabulous Madrid.  

The crew at utopic US will give you plenty of good reasons to join this coworking space:  you always have willing people to help you during your work day, you will be a part of a creative community of transformative minds, there are 3 unique coworking spaces where you can hold your meetings, events and continue your professional training, plus the in-house team can cover all the fiscal and accounting needs of your project.  

Multiple services are on offer from tax advice to accounting and consulting.  You can grab a space in an open coworking environment or if you want a bit of seclusion, then you can commandeer your own private office.  There are plenty of courses and events on offer to inspire, transform and enjoy, plus a training school to keep you on your toes and up-todate in a collaborative learning environment.

There are breakfast meetings once a week to interact with your coworkers between mouthfuls, monthly picnic events more like potluck dinners and plenty of after work get-togethers to join in for some gossip. 

Attracting freelancers, entrepreneurs, small companies and digital nomads to its doors, utopic US can help you in any sphere from developing ideas and projects to the creation of a virtual company, if you wish.

fields.address: 10 Calle de Walia, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: utopic_US Conde de Casal is a coworking space in Madrid. Here, you can find your own coworking space, with options that vary from private to shared office spaces and meeting rooms. utopic_US can be not only the place you come and get your work done, but also the place you come and meet new people and make some friends. Your personal development can benefit from the training schools they have on the premise, and the community of professionals gathering here every day. Some other services available for you here are virtual office services, tax advice, accounting and advertising services. Does this sound like the right coworking space for you?

fields.address: 9 Calle de la Colegiata, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: Once you become a part of the community at utopic_US Collegiata, chance are that you may never want to leave it. Located in the center of Madrid, utopic_US came to life in an old commercial gallery. Freelancers, startups and professionals get to enjoy fully equipped offices with ergonomic furniture, reception service, meeting rooms and access to workshops and events. Oh, and did we mention the location? Being in the center of one of the greatest cities in the world grants you access to the coolest restaurants, food trucks and pubs where you can enjoy a glass of wine after work. Become a member today!

fields.address: 42 Calle de Manuel Tovar, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: Urban Lab Madrid is both a coworking space and business center located in Madrid. Whether you’re a start-up entrepreneur, a freelancer or an independent professional, this can be the opportunity for you to change your working environment and choose to give coworking a try. The offices vary from private or small offices to shared spaces, meeting and multipurpose rooms and virtual offices. All the offices here are fully equipped with all the necessary equipment for a productive day of work. The facilities available vary from printing and photocopying equipment, to faxes and scanners. Other available services for you here include support services for entrepreneurs, translation and interpretation services and multilingual phone support. Or you can come and see for yourself all that Urban Lab has to offer.

fields.address: 94 Calle de Blasco de Garay, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description:
Union Coworking is an upscale coworking space located north of the Centro neighborhood of Madrid. This coworking space has a techie vibe with lots of the members working with technologies that would make the eyes of non-technical workers glaze over.

Many of the members here work as developers, web designers, and there’s even a web hosting company based out of the coworking space. Don’t let the many techies scare you off though. You’ll be able to find friends and network here regardless of the industry you’re working in.

Plus, the community is only one aspect of Union Coworking. Perhaps even more important is the coworking space itself. Built to hold just 13 members, the coworking area is pretty cosy. There’s also a comfortable amount of space between all of the workstations.

Aside from the coworking area, other spaces are included in your membership as well. The rest room, terrace, and meeting room for example, are all available to members of the community.

Other amenities include complimentary water and coffee, security, ergonomic chairs, all utility fees, daily cleaning, plus free scanning services (printing and copying are available too at a low cost to you).

Joining this synergistic coworking space as a coworking member will set you back just 150€/month.

fields.address: 179 Paseo de la Castellana, Madrid, Spain
fields.cs_description: Unifortia is a coworking space especially intended for lawyers and legal professionals. The spaces available here vary from private offices, meeting rooms, open coworking areas, semi-enclosed offices and a training room. All the offices here have speedy cable and WIFI internet and air conditioning. Your access to all these amenities provided here vary on the renting plan you choose. Other services available for you here are telesecretary, email handling and domain registration. You can have it all under one roof. Unifortia is also a place where you can connect with other like-minded professionals like you. Don’t take our word for it, come and take a look yourself.

fields.address: E 3rd Ring Road North, Chaoyang District, Beijing, China
fields.cs_description:
A co-living and coworking setup, Yioho in Beijing gives you the ultimate pad of having your home and office in one.  This will be heaven for the lovers of stylish design not just in your "bedroom" but also in the office environment where shared desks are in an uncluttered funky space of clean lines, sparkling white and splashed with bright colors like an artist's palette.

China's sprawling capital, Beijing has a history stretching over 3 millennia and is a wonderland of old and new architecture from the ancient Forbidden City complex to the massive Tiananmen Square.  

Perfect for the budding entrepreneur, digital nomad looking for a home for a while or a fledgling startup team to gather, Yioho offers daily cleaning services, IT support and fully furnished offices with a professional vibe that will have you smiling all the way to your laptop each day.

There is plenty of tea and coffee on hand to keep the brain waves happening, super fast Wi-Fi to plug in to and all the office gadgets available that you could possibly need.  Melding function with efficiency you can arrange for 1 bedroom and 2 workstations for a reasonable monthly fee.  Sign up for a year and butler service is complimentary for that initial period plus you will have free access to the meeting rooms and all areas will be customized to your preferences.  

What more could you want?

fields.address: 18th Floor Wudaokou Yousheng Building, Haidian District, Beijing, China
fields.space_name: Wu Jie Space - Wu Dao Kou
fields.cs_description: Wu Jie Space - Wu Dao Kou coworking in Beijing welcomes freelancers, professionals and talented workers to shared their knowledge and experience. The space promotes a modern and simple design, as it is located in a 1000 sq m facility. With a unique style, all walls are painted in white, thus leaving space for colorful decorations. fields.cs_description:
Naming themselves as a "startup accelerator", XNode offers opportunities to collaborate and network with their organized events where clients looking for funding can pitch ideas to venture capitalists. If you a chasing an inroad into Shanghai's burgeoning entrepreneurial community, this is definitely the place to hang out whilst working. 

Sitting near the Jing ‘an Temple, the venue is easy to find whether you are arriving by public transport, pedalling a bicycle or pounding the pavement.  Not only can you satisfy your work needs but your hunger pangs as well with its on-site cafe that is open from 9am to 6pm weekdays.  This is especially for those that require plenty of caffeine hits during the day to keep the brain waves happening. 

The doors are open 24/7 so anyone that is a workaholic will be wearing a huge grin as they can work to their own rhythm and whims. Aimed at the digital nomads meandering around the globe, budding startups and innovative entrepreneurs, you will find clever individuals from all industries to rub shoulders with.  You can take over 1 of the 30 seats in the bustling shared area that is decked out with tables and lounge chairs.  It is a cafe type of space with private meeting rooms that can be hired by the hour for those important one-on-one interviews or meetings amongst clients or cohorts that you want to keep under wraps.  If you need to see your words on paper, printing is available as well as other office gadgets that you may require.  The Wi-Fi is super fast to keep you connected but you will have to poke your nose into a corner to find a socket if you need to recharge items.  To get around this issue sign up for a monthly fixed desk with its own socket and all the problems are solved.

You will be given a tour of the entire space when you initially visit XNode to get you acclimatised. The friendly front desk can speak both Chinese and English so you won't experience any lost in translation moments.

fields.address: 968 Jin Zhong Road, Changning District, Shanghai, China
fields.cs_description:
SOHO3Q - Sky 3Q is another coworking space under the umbrella of the guru company of office and real estate in China, SOHO.  Crossing the boundaries of real estate and the Internet economy, this company is focusing on the remote working market for the mobile generation of tech savvy individuals. Attracting the 20 something mobile working crowd en masse in Shanghai, there is no age detector at the door if you a bit longer in the tooth.  

Created as an ecosystem for the collaboration between diverse communities from various backgrounds, SOHO3Q is a community-orientated company with plenty of experience to create that perfect space for entrepreneurs, startups and digital nomads to flock to.  SOHO3Q has over 2,500 hot desks dotted around Beijing and Shanghai under their funky roofs with more in the pipeline for the future.
The venue at Lingkong 3Q, as with all of their other venues, is awash in exciting decor with a minimalist approach and seriously bright colors to create a dynamic and vibrant atmosphere.  Once you become a member it is easy to find an available desk at any one of their venues via an on-line portal.  With this app in hand you can pay your dues, book a desk or an office, reserve a conference room, register a guest and find out about what event or function is in the pipeline that you may pique your interest.

The hot desks have plenty of room to flap your wings and you will be provided with your own personal locker to hide your personal goodies in.  There is super fast Wi-Fi to keep you connected and you will have an allocated number of complimentary conference room hours.  Private phone booths are available and there is a vending machine to throw coins into when your stomach cries out for a snack attack and you can't be bothered showing off your prowess in the share kitchen.  The caffeine addict will be happy, as there is plenty of coffee on tap to keep the shakes at bay.

When your brain implodes or you are just feeling lazy there is a lounge area where you can chill out.

fields.address: 600 Zhapu Road, Hongkou District, Shanghai, China
fields.cs_description:
Shanghai, a bustling IT hub, will have you reeling with shivers of excitement maybe because of the work possibilities, but definitely when you run away from your work desk into the fray of its streets.  Mysterious and exotic, this cosmopolitan city overflows with Buddhist temples, Jewish synagogues, art deco buildings and skyscrapers spearing the clouds.  Begging to be explored, you can indulge in some of the best restaurants in the world or munch on dumplings street side.   

There are a handful of well-known companies in China absorbing the coworking space market, of which SOHO is one.  They have had plenty of experience in what a coworker is looking for, so you can be assured that every one of their venues is in total harmony with the needs of digital nomads, startups and budding entrepreneurs.  From inspired interiors to the necessary office infrastructure, nothing has been overlooked.

You can choose from a fully furnished office decked out how you like if you want to work alone or if you need to accommodate a team of bodies.  Alternatively you can have a dedicated desk with its own cabinet to stash your personal goodies in for those that are into sharing.  You won't be sitting on top of your cohorts and you will have plenty of elbow space if you are in the habit of flapping your wings whilst working.  For those that know exactly what they want and are not interested in checking the premises out first, you can book on-line with no hassles.

Spaces can be rented by the week or by the month and the doors are open from 8am to 9pm Monday to Friday and from 9am to 6pm at the weekends for those that don't want to play up or have a lazy sleep-in.  There is super fast Wi-Fi to plug into, complimentary coffee to make the caffeine addicts smile all day, a vending machine for instant hunger gratification or if you can't be bothered whipping up a treat in the kitchen, plus an allocated amount of printing and copying.  There is a phone booth to run to when you want to have a private conversation on the telephone and when the brain is on overload there is a lounge area to contemplate your toes.  

You can rent by the week or by the month and once you join you can use your "conference room" hours at any of SOHO's locations.

fields.address: Floor 2-4, Building D, 388 Ma Dang Road, Huangpu District, Shanghai, China
fields.cs_description:
Creating perfect work places for Shanghai's local IT bodies, remote workers, fledgling startups and budding entrepreneurs, SOHO is one of a few companies in China invading this niche market.  They are now experts in what to provide for a friendly and welcoming space from the funky and hip interiors to having a professional platform of resources as well as numerous events on a weekly basis. 

The exotic city that conjures up images of dumplings and noodles, bustling laneways and colorful markets, Shanghai is cosmopolitan and dynamic.  When you want to run away from your work, you will never be at a loss for something to do from gawking at its incredible array of architecture to swanning around art galleries or hitting the throbbing nightlife scene.  

If you want to check out the venue before committing yourself, you can book a tour on-line.  If you really do know what you want, you can just hit the button on-line and take up residence straight away. The fully furnished office spaces come in various sizes depending on how many bodies you want to accommodate.  You may be the type that wants to float in your own bubble or need to accommodate cohorts all working on the same project.  If you are the sharing and caring type that likes to rub shoulders with your neighbors, then a designated desk area may be right for you.  You will have your own cabinet to lock your personal goodies in and heaps of elbowroom if you tend to spread out when working.

It is possible to rent by the week or by the month and credit cards are accepted if you don't want to use your precious cash.  As a part of your fee you will have a number of complimentary "conference room" hours that can be used at any one of SOHO's coworking space locations throughout the city.  There is super fast Wi-Fi to keep you connected and plenty of caffeine shots to keep avid coffee lovers smiling and happy.  A vending machine is available if you want an instant hunger gratification or you can whip up a meal in the open-plan kitchen if you want something more substantial and can't be bothered hitting the streets for some curbside cuisine.  A phone booth is available for those private conversations and you will have an allocated amount of printing and copying for when you want words on paper.  When you get to breaking point, there is a lounge area to chill in.  

The doors are open from 8am to 9pm Monday to Friday and from 9am to 6pm at the weekends for the workaholics to thrive.
